      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was performed through benchmark comparisons with analytical solutions for laminar pipe flow and lid-driven cavity problems. Results confirm solver implementation is consistent with published verification cases at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (4.2M, 9.7M, and 18.4M elements) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for the hemolysis index quantity of interest was less than 2.1%, satisfying the MRL 2 requirement and exceeding it to gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA benchmark pump study are well-characterized with documented flow rates, rotational speeds, and fluid properties (glycerol-saline blood analog). Temperature, viscosity, and inlet turbulence conditions are matched to simulation boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values are compared against experimental measurements across all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error is 8.3%, within the 15% acceptance threshold. Pressure rise predictions agree within 5% of measured values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index, RH) is directly relevant to the clinical decision context. The power law hemolysis model outputs scalar hemolysis exposure values that map directly to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1 relative to predicate device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under the same flow-speed operating envelope as the COU. Blood analog fluid is used in both validation experiments and clinical device testing, ensuring high relevance of validation evidence to the intended use."
    },
    {
